cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IOT, cs.CV, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a novel machine learning model for analyzing heterogeneous multivariate temporal data obtained from sensors in IoT applications. The model uses attention mechanisms and LSTM networks to model temporal and non-linear relationships. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IOT (Internet of Things). The paper also includes experiments on activity recognition and environment monitoring datasets, which suggest a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
